'''Mikashikiyahime''' (三炊屋媛, dates unknown) was an ancient Japanese woman.
== Overview == In the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]], she is referred to as '''Tomiyabime''' (登美夜毘売), while the [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]] calls her '''Mikashikiyahime''' (三炊屋媛), '''Torimiyahime''' (鳥見屋媛), or '''Nagasunehime''' (長髄媛). She is also known by names such as '''Mishikiyahime''' (御炊屋姫), '''Kushitama-hime-no-Mikoto''' (櫛玉姫命), or '''Kushitama-hime''' (櫛玉比売命).
== Lineage == Mikashikiyahime was the sister of {{ill|Nagatsuhiko|lt=Nagatsuhiko|lt=Nagasunehiko|ja|長髄彦|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasunehiko|qq=}} and the wife of {{ill|Nigihayahi|ja|饒速日命|lt=Nigihayahi no Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nigihayahi|qq=}}. Together, they had a son, {{ill|Umashimaji|lt=Umashimaji|lt=Umashimaji no Mikoto|ja|宇摩志麻遅命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Umashimaji no Mikoto|qq=}}, who became the ancestral deity of the [[:en:Mononobe clan|Mononobe clan]] and {{ill|Hozumi clan|ja|穂積氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hozumi clan|qq=}}.<ref name="#3"/>
== Shrines == Mikashikiyahime is enshrined at several locations: * {{ill|Ishikiri Tsurugiya Shrine|ja|石切剣箭神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ishikiri Tsurugiya Shrine|qq=}}: Within the {{ill|Upper Shrine (Ishikiri Tsurugiya Shrine)|ja|石切剣箭神社#上之社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Upper Shrine (Ishikiri Tsurugiya Shrine)|qq=}}, specifically at the Tomireisha and {{ill|Fudō Shrine|ja|婦道神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fudō Shrine|qq=}} (Higashi-Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture). * {{ill|Yataza Kushitama Hikojinja|ja|矢田坐久志玉比古神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yataza Kushitama Hikojinja|qq=}} * {{ill|Kushitama Hime-no-Mikoto Shrine|ja|櫛玉比女命神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kushitama Hime-no-Mikoto Shrine|qq=}}
