== Lineage == Mikashikiyahime was the sister of {{ill|Nagatsuhiko|lt=Nagatsuhiko|lt=Nagasunehiko|ja|長髄彦|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasunehiko|qq=}} and the wife of {{ill|Nigihayahi|ja|饒速日命|lt=Nigihayahi no Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nigihayahi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ニギハヤヒ}}. Together, they had a son, {{ill|Umashimaji|lt=Umashimaji|lt=Umashimaji no Mikoto|ja|宇摩志麻遅命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Umashimaji no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ウマシマジ}}, who became the ancestral deity of the [[:en:Mononobe clan|Mononobe clan]] and {{ill|Hozumi clan|ja|穂積氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hozumi clan|qq=}}.<ref name="#3"/>
== Shrines == Mikashikiyahime is enshrined at several locations: * {{ill|Ishikiri Tsurugiya Shrine|ja|石切剣箭神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ishikiri Tsurugiya Shrine|qq=}}: Within the {{ill|Upper Shrine (Ishikiri Tsurugiya Shrine)|ja|石切剣箭神社#上之社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Upper Shrine (Ishikiri Tsurugiya Shrine)|qq=|1=Ishikiri Tsurugiya Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11585189}}, specifically at the Tomireisha and {{ill|Fudō Shrine|ja|婦道神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fudō Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (Higashi-Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture). * {{ill|Yataza Kushitama Hikojinja|ja|矢田坐久志玉比古神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yataza Kushitama Hikojinja|qq=|1=Yata ni Imasu Kushitamahiko Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11584205}} * {{ill|Kushitama Hime-no-Mikoto Shrine|ja|櫛玉比女命神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kushitama Hime-no-Mikoto Shrine|qq=}}
